<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 9:44PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Roosevelt, southeastern Valley, McCone, northwestern Dawson and
northwestern Richland Counties through 1045 PM MDT...
At 944 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles southwest of Vida, or 20 miles northwest of Circle, moving east
at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Wolf Point, Poplar, Circle, Richey, Bloomfield, Vida, Brockway,
Oswego and Weldon.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
